      <h1>About</h1>
      <p>
        I'm <strong>Xand Reed</strong>. I build <a href="https://github.com/xandreeddev/efferent">efferent</a>,
        an open-source coding agent that lives in the terminal: Effect.ts and Bun underneath, a modal
        multi-pane TUI on OpenTUI and SolidJS on top, multi-provider through
        <code>@effect/ai</code>, and evals colocated with the code they judge.
      </p>
      <p>
        The bet behind both the agent and this blog: <em>AI engineering is still engineering.</em>
        Capabilities should be services with typed errors, provider choice should be runtime state
        rather than architecture, and an agent without evals is a demo. Everything here is built in
        public — posts lead with an artifact (a diff, a benchmark, an eval run), not an opinion.
      </p>
      <p>And no React. Not on the blog, not in the terminal.</p>
